data.title: Xiaomi is back on top in wearable band market in 2025 with 18% share, followed by Apple with 17% and Huawei with 16%.
data.description: In 2025, global shipments of wearable devices surpassed 200 million units, marking a 6% increase from the previous year as reported by Omdia. Xiaomi regained the leading position, holding an 18% market share and becoming the largest wearable vendor by annual shipments, a title it last held in 2020. Apple closely followed in second place with 17%, while Huawei secured the third spot with 16%. The market is witnessing a trend of consolidation, with the top five vendors, including Samsung (9%) and Garmin, dominating the industry.

data.title: Frontline (FRO) beats Q4 earnings estimates by 0.98% with EPS of $1.03, revenue up $198.86 million from last year.
data.description: Frontline, traded on NYSE under the symbol FRO, released its Q4 earnings report on Friday, February 27, 2026, at 02:00 AM. The company exceeded estimated earnings by 0.98%, with an EPS of $1.03 compared to the expected $1.02. Revenue saw a significant increase of $198.86 million compared to the previous year. In the last quarter, Frontline did not meet the earnings expectations. For more details, the complete article can be found on Benzinga.com.

data.title: JBT Marel completed a major renovation of its Customer Innovation Center in Lakeland, Florida, becoming the premier destination for sustainable food tech.
data.description: In Lakeland, Florida, JBT Marel, a leading provider of advanced automation solutions for the food and beverage sector, has revealed its updated Customer Innovation Center. The revamped facility serves as the company's main customer hub for sustainable food technology, covering the entire production process from fresh produce to ready-to-eat meals, beverages, and dairy products. With numerous CIC locations globally, JBT Marel's facilities offer customers the opportunity to collaborate closely with specialists.

data.title: Ethereum Foundation introduces Project Odin for sustainable funding, embedding advisors with key teams like Vyper. Initial cohort already underway.
data.description: A 12-month program by EF involves embedding advisors within critical infrastructure teams such as Vyper to establish sustainable funding methods beyond grants. The inaugural cohort of this program is currently in progress.

data.title: CW BANCORP announces $0.23 quarterly dividend, payable on April 1, 2026.
data.description: In Irvine, California on February 27, 2026, CW BANCORP (OTCQX: CWBK), the parent company of CommerceWest Bank, disclosed that its Board of Directors has sanctioned a quarterly cash dividend. data.title: Atrium Therapeutics raised $270M to develop RNA medicines for rare genetic cardiomyopathies, targeting PRKAG2 and PLN syndromes.
data.description: A new branch resulting from Novartis AG's purchase of Avidity Biosciences is making progress in specialized cardiology initiatives through a focused RNA delivery system. Key candidates ATR 1072 and ATR 1086 are slated to start clinical trials for PRKAG2 syndrome and PLN cardiomyopathy. The development is centered in San Diego and was announced on February 27th.
